1
00:02:49,760 --> 00:02:52,279
- Let go of me.
- I won't. I love you.

2
00:02:52,280 --> 00:02:53,760
Let Ms. Pat go right now.

3
00:02:54,360 --> 00:02:55,720
Mr. Phum.

4
00:02:56,240 --> 00:03:00,040
Or maybe Mook disappeared because of...

5
00:03:05,320 --> 00:03:06,560
What's happening?

6
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:12,000
Ghosts are crawling out of the graves!

7
00:03:12,680 --> 00:03:14,200
Mr. Narathon!

8
00:03:15,280 --> 00:03:17,479
Mr. Narathon, can you hear me?

9
00:03:17,480 --> 00:03:18,960
I'm in here.

10
00:04:55,040 --> 00:04:57,040
You can't run away from me, Kaimook.

11
00:05:10,440 --> 00:05:12,559
You have to stay with me.

12
00:05:12,560 --> 00:05:16,880
Kaimook, you're going to
stay with me forever.

13
00:05:29,680 --> 00:05:31,559
Kliang, you don't need to go with us.

14
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:34,399
Let Na drive instead.
We don't know how many days we'll be gone.

15
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:37,479
You stay here
and help Kaew take care of the house.

16
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:38,399
Alright?

17
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:39,640
Yes, sir.

18
00:05:50,480 --> 00:05:51,920
- Hello.
- Hello.

19
00:05:52,440 --> 00:05:53,720
Is Kaimook home?

20
00:05:54,240 --> 00:05:56,079
Do you need something
from Kaimook, Mr. Phum?

21
00:05:56,080 --> 00:05:59,559
I came to invite Kaimook
and all of you to my gallery opening.

22
00:05:59,560 --> 00:06:01,919
Most of the works displayed there
are photographs taken by Kaimook.

23
00:06:01,920 --> 00:06:04,039
I hope all of you
will honor me by attending.

24
00:06:04,040 --> 00:06:05,160
Yes.

25
00:06:09,080 --> 00:06:13,320
An art exhibition and charity auction?

26
00:06:13,920 --> 00:06:16,400
In the end, it all goes straight
into your own pocket anyway.

27
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:18,680
You misunderstand me.

28
00:06:19,840 --> 00:06:22,320
I understand you perfectly well.

29
00:06:23,880 --> 00:06:27,480
Even when your own son could be
dead or alive, you don't even care.

30
00:06:29,200 --> 00:06:32,599
Sorry,
we don't have time for your nonsense.

31
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:33,560
Let's go.

32
00:06:35,640 --> 00:06:37,079
Excuse us.

33
00:06:37,080 --> 00:06:38,040
Come on.

34
00:06:42,320 --> 00:06:44,679
Sorry, sir. I have to go too.

35
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:47,560
Wait. What's going on?

36
00:06:48,840 --> 00:06:50,360
What happened to Narathon?

37
00:06:51,160 --> 00:06:53,959
Everyone who went to the research center
on Skull Island has disappeared.

38
00:06:53,960 --> 00:06:55,640
Right now, no one can contact them at all.

39
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:43,719
Where is everyone?

40
00:07:43,720 --> 00:07:45,600
It's almost afternoon already.

41
00:07:50,760 --> 00:07:53,759
Oh, where's Ms. Kaimook?

42
00:07:53,760 --> 00:07:55,720
Didn't you find her?

43
00:07:58,880 --> 00:08:00,279
We still haven't found her.

44
00:08:00,280 --> 00:08:02,879
We searched all the way
to the back of the island,

45
00:08:02,880 --> 00:08:04,440
but there's still no sign of her.

46
00:08:06,400 --> 00:08:12,760
And didn't the female ghost
lead you to Ms. Kaimook?

47
00:08:14,720 --> 00:08:15,960
She did.

48
00:08:16,760 --> 00:08:19,599
But we found nine graves instead

49
00:08:19,600 --> 00:08:21,480
and we encountered other ghosts too.

50
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:24,519
Luckily we made it back.

51
00:08:24,520 --> 00:08:26,200
We barely survived.

52
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:32,880
So the nine graves
really do exist on this island?

53
00:08:34,240 --> 00:08:37,320
You know about those graves?

54
00:08:38,360 --> 00:08:43,240
I overheard the previous research team
talking about them once.

55
00:08:44,360 --> 00:08:46,480
Why were they talking about it?

56
00:08:47,080 --> 00:08:48,719
It sounded like

57
00:08:48,720 --> 00:08:52,519
someone found an old journal
at the old research center.

58
00:08:52,520 --> 00:08:54,160
They were reading it together.

59
00:08:55,560 --> 00:08:59,720
I only heard bits and pieces
while serving coffee,

60
00:09:01,160 --> 00:09:03,960
but I never thought it was true.

61
00:09:04,480 --> 00:09:06,919
That means if we can find that journal,

62
00:09:06,920 --> 00:09:10,160
there may be clues
that can help us find Kaimook.

63
00:09:12,040 --> 00:09:12,920
Right.

64
00:09:13,880 --> 00:09:16,319
Then let's go search for it.
Where is it, Auntie?

65
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:17,720
This way, please.

66
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:40,680
These are all just general records.

67
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:43,960
These are all summaries of underwater
coral reef restoration research.

68
00:09:47,680 --> 00:09:51,760
There are only books
about coral reef restoration.

69
00:10:27,240 --> 00:10:28,400
A journal?

70
00:10:31,600 --> 00:10:32,720
You found it?

71
00:10:36,120 --> 00:10:37,120
Yes.

72
00:10:39,880 --> 00:10:43,920
It looks like an ordinary diary.

73
00:10:50,480 --> 00:10:52,400
But this note
from the second day is interesting.

74
00:10:54,760 --> 00:10:55,920
Read it.

75
00:10:58,960 --> 00:11:01,360
"Tonight, we heard strange sounds,

76
00:11:01,880 --> 00:11:03,760
like the sound of a ship."

77
00:11:04,480 --> 00:11:06,639
"But when we went outside to check,
there was nothing there."

78
00:11:06,640 --> 00:11:09,079
"Could it be the island's curse,

79
00:11:09,080 --> 00:11:12,399
just as the rumors say

80
00:11:12,400 --> 00:11:15,559
about the ghost ship
that often appears before sailors

81
00:11:15,560 --> 00:11:18,199
and travelers near Skull Island?"

82
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:21,920
"They say the ship
once belonged to pirates."

83
00:11:23,280 --> 00:11:25,120
Hurry up!

84
00:11:46,920 --> 00:11:48,999
I surrender. I'm scared.

85
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:50,719
I surrender. Please don't hurt me.

86
00:11:50,720 --> 00:11:53,480
Please don't kill me. I don't want to die.

87
00:11:56,080 --> 00:11:57,440
Please. I surrender.

88
00:12:01,280 --> 00:12:02,520
Please don't.

89
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:44,640
Hey!

90
00:12:48,360 --> 00:12:49,280
Hey?!

91
00:13:10,600 --> 00:13:11,799
"But then,

92
00:13:11,800 --> 00:13:15,079
the pirate ship suddenly vanished
without a trace."

93
00:13:15,080 --> 00:13:18,520
"Also, a government ship transporting
ancient gold treasures was robbed."

94
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:20,959
"It is believed that, driven by greed,

95
00:13:20,960 --> 00:13:23,959
the pirates betrayed one another

96
00:13:23,960 --> 00:13:26,880
and killed each other on Skull Island."

97
00:13:27,520 --> 00:13:29,400
My goodness.

98
00:13:30,680 --> 00:13:34,239
Does that mean the nine graves we saw

99
00:13:34,240 --> 00:13:37,200
and those ghosts were the pirates?

100
00:13:37,720 --> 00:13:38,999
My goodness.

101
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:43,039
So there really are ghosts on this island?

102
00:13:43,040 --> 00:13:44,960
And Ms. Kaimook disappeared

103
00:13:45,560 --> 00:13:47,159
because the ghosts took her away?

104
00:13:47,160 --> 00:13:48,799
I think

105
00:13:48,800 --> 00:13:51,119
we should leave this island

106
00:13:51,120 --> 00:13:52,879
- as quickly as possible.
- Yes.

107
00:13:52,880 --> 00:13:54,239
- Please.
- Yes.

108
00:13:54,240 --> 00:13:56,799
We should notify
the rescue team or the police

109
00:13:56,800 --> 00:13:59,640
and let them help
search for Ms. Kaimook instead.

110
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:02,879
I tried calling several times
since this morning,

111
00:14:02,880 --> 00:14:05,760
but the phone didn't work

112
00:14:10,560 --> 00:14:11,960
There's no phone signal either.

113
00:14:13,240 --> 00:14:14,879
It's like we're stranded on this island.

114
00:14:14,880 --> 00:14:16,440
We're screwed.

115
00:14:19,720 --> 00:14:20,920
Don't worry.

116
00:14:22,280 --> 00:14:25,600
The boat that dropped the staff off
should return around three this afternoon.

117
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:29,560
So, you can go pack your things.

118
00:14:30,160 --> 00:14:31,759
- Thank you.
- Auntie, let's go.

119
00:14:31,760 --> 00:14:34,080
- Let's go pack.
- Let's go.

120
00:14:39,680 --> 00:14:40,760
Hey.

121
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:44,640
You're not planning
to leave this island, are you?

122
00:14:47,440 --> 00:14:48,520
No.

123
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:51,560
Take everyone back first.

124
00:14:52,160 --> 00:14:54,200
Report everything to the police
and get them here.

125
00:14:55,520 --> 00:14:56,840
As for me,

126
00:14:59,160 --> 00:15:00,600
I'll keep searching for Kaimook.

127
00:15:04,720 --> 00:15:05,840
Hey.

128
00:15:07,280 --> 00:15:09,040
Then I'm staying with you.

129
00:15:10,040 --> 00:15:11,320
I'll help you find Kaimook.

130
00:15:21,960 --> 00:15:23,040
Ms. Da,

131
00:15:23,920 --> 00:15:25,720
you should go prepare too.

132
00:15:29,280 --> 00:15:30,919
If you two are going to stay,

133
00:15:30,920 --> 00:15:32,440
you need me too.

134
00:15:40,200 --> 00:15:42,200
Mook and I
have been friends for a long time.

135
00:15:42,840 --> 00:15:44,480
Sure, we fight sometimes,

136
00:15:45,160 --> 00:15:48,760
but I can't abandon the friend
who once saved my life.

137
00:16:00,400 --> 00:16:01,320
Well.

138
00:16:03,680 --> 00:16:06,080
I'm really sorry.

139
00:16:06,680 --> 00:16:09,039
I didn't want to leave you behind.

140
00:16:09,040 --> 00:16:11,439
Honestly, if it were anything else,
I'd fight to the death.

141
00:16:11,440 --> 00:16:14,920
But ghosts...

142
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:18,000
Don't worry about it, Auntie.

143
00:16:18,720 --> 00:16:20,999
After everything that happened,

144
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:23,479
I don't want everyone
risking their lives here either.

145
00:16:23,480 --> 00:16:25,439
As soon as we reach the mainland,

146
00:16:25,440 --> 00:16:28,959
we'll notify the police and rescue teams
to come help.

147
00:16:28,960 --> 00:16:30,399
Thank you.

148
00:16:30,400 --> 00:16:33,639
Also, there's still instant food
in the kitchen.

149
00:16:33,640 --> 00:16:36,600
Canned food too. I stocked up quite a lot.

150
00:16:37,560 --> 00:16:38,999
Don't worry, Auntie.

151
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:40,639
We'll take care of ourselves.

152
00:16:40,640 --> 00:16:43,039
- Then I'll get going now.
- Okay.

153
00:16:43,040 --> 00:16:44,239
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

154
00:16:44,240 --> 00:16:45,399
Goodbye.

155
00:16:45,400 --> 00:16:46,560
Safe travels.

156
00:16:55,520 --> 00:16:57,400
Let's prepare to save Kaimook.

157
00:17:01,480 --> 00:17:03,520
I need to go grab my things
from my room first.

158
00:17:04,560 --> 00:17:06,480
Thon and I will go prepare too.

159
00:17:08,240 --> 00:17:09,160
Let's go.

160
00:18:36,840 --> 00:18:40,360
Buddy, are we really
going to use guns to fight ghosts?

161
00:18:42,800 --> 00:18:44,560
Still better than going empty-handed.

162
00:18:48,120 --> 00:18:49,279
If I'd known this,

163
00:18:49,280 --> 00:18:52,520
I would've brought holy amulets
from every monk possible.

164
00:18:56,520 --> 00:18:58,800
Let's just call it a life experience.

165
00:18:59,520 --> 00:19:01,640
At least we'll have something
to tell our grandkids someday.

166
00:19:04,360 --> 00:19:08,600
<i>Sathu.</i> Please, let us make it out alive.

167
00:19:13,200 --> 00:19:14,720
Thanks, my friend.

168
00:19:16,320 --> 00:19:17,640
For not abandoning me.

169
00:19:24,120 --> 00:19:27,720
How could I abandon you
when you refuse to abandon my student?

170
00:19:29,560 --> 00:19:33,080
You seem even more worried
about her lately than I am.

171
00:19:35,680 --> 00:19:37,880
I'm worried about everyone.

172
00:19:39,160 --> 00:19:40,800
Hurry and finish packing.

173
00:19:41,400 --> 00:19:42,719
Trying to dodge the subject?

174
00:19:42,720 --> 00:19:45,320
You think I can't tell, Narathon?

175
00:19:47,440 --> 00:19:48,800
Go pack your things.

176
00:19:50,040 --> 00:19:53,040
Fine. I'll go prepare food supplies.

177
00:20:09,480 --> 00:20:11,280
Didn't you say
you weren't scared of ghosts?

178
00:20:13,160 --> 00:20:16,440
Anyone would be scared
in a place like this.

179
00:20:16,960 --> 00:20:18,839
Good thing I ran into you.

180
00:20:18,840 --> 00:20:21,880
If I'd walked here alone,
I would've run too.

181
00:20:26,600 --> 00:20:28,080
What are you laughing at?

182
00:20:29,880 --> 00:20:31,600
At you.

183
00:20:33,040 --> 00:20:35,200
You just don't seem like the type
who'd be scared of ghosts.

184
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:39,360
Are you complimenting me or insulting me?

185
00:20:39,960 --> 00:20:40,760
I'm complimenting you.

186
00:20:43,560 --> 00:20:48,119
If I said someone like you
doesn't need to fear ghosts,

187
00:20:48,120 --> 00:20:50,560
that would definitely sound offensive.

188
00:20:51,400 --> 00:20:52,680
How?

189
00:20:55,440 --> 00:20:57,119
Back in school,

190
00:20:57,120 --> 00:21:00,800
my friend used to tease girls
who were afraid of ghosts

191
00:21:02,040 --> 00:21:03,320
by saying,

192
00:21:03,920 --> 00:21:06,080
"With a face like yours,

193
00:21:06,600 --> 00:21:08,760
even ghosts would run away."

194
00:21:10,200 --> 00:21:14,280
You don't seem like
someone who'd tell jokes either.

195
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:17,560
Are you complimenting me
or insulting me now?

196
00:21:18,160 --> 00:21:20,280
I'm complimenting you.

197
00:21:23,240 --> 00:21:24,720
So you're not scared anymore?

198
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:28,920
I'm not afraid of anything anymore.

199
00:21:33,400 --> 00:21:34,840
Let's go then.

200
00:21:35,440 --> 00:21:36,320
Okay.

201
00:21:42,040 --> 00:21:43,240
This is my fault.

202
00:21:46,240 --> 00:21:47,440
I'm sorry, Kaimook.

203
00:21:50,040 --> 00:21:51,320
If you'd been afraid,

204
00:21:53,120 --> 00:21:55,560
you probably wouldn't have left your room

205
00:21:57,200 --> 00:21:58,920
no matter what you heard.

206
00:22:02,600 --> 00:22:03,680
I'm sorry.

207
00:22:08,800 --> 00:22:10,040
But I promise,

208
00:22:13,520 --> 00:22:15,160
I'll bring you back no matter what.

209
00:22:39,760 --> 00:22:40,800
Did you get a boat?

210
00:22:41,800 --> 00:22:43,279
They agree to go to other islands.

211
00:22:43,280 --> 00:22:45,479
But no one will go to Skull island, Dad.

212
00:22:45,480 --> 00:22:47,800
Even when I offered
two or three times the money.

213
00:22:48,560 --> 00:22:51,039
- My goodness.
- That's crazy.

214
00:22:51,040 --> 00:22:52,520
What are we going to do?

215
00:22:55,280 --> 00:22:57,440
No.

216
00:23:00,040 --> 00:23:01,000
He's a madman.

217
00:23:18,320 --> 00:23:19,760
He must be hungry.

218
00:23:37,440 --> 00:23:39,680
A woman... fell into the sea.

219
00:23:47,400 --> 00:23:48,959
Here.

220
00:23:48,960 --> 00:23:51,720
Take it. Don't be afraid.

221
00:23:52,520 --> 00:23:54,040
Use it to buy food.

222
00:23:55,840 --> 00:23:57,240
Woman!

223
00:23:59,840 --> 00:24:02,040
A woman fell into the sea.

224
00:24:02,760 --> 00:24:06,119
- She disappeared.
- No.

225
00:24:06,120 --> 00:24:07,639
I'm not trying to hurt you.

226
00:24:07,640 --> 00:24:09,119
This is for you.

227
00:24:09,120 --> 00:24:11,079
Use it to buy food.

228
00:24:11,080 --> 00:24:12,280
Food, okay?

229
00:24:13,600 --> 00:24:15,640
Okay?

230
00:24:28,280 --> 00:24:30,000
Our family has always done good.

231
00:24:30,760 --> 00:24:32,800
Why did something terrible
have to happen to Kaimook?

232
00:24:34,360 --> 00:24:36,360
We can't even find a boat to go save her.

233
00:24:45,440 --> 00:24:47,320
Dad, look over there.

234
00:24:48,920 --> 00:24:50,680
Should we try asking them for help?

235
00:24:52,640 --> 00:24:53,880
- Let's go.
- Okay.

236
00:24:57,320 --> 00:24:59,920
Don't go! Don't go!

237
00:25:01,480 --> 00:25:05,799
You'll die.

238
00:25:05,800 --> 00:25:07,760
Don't go!

239
00:25:13,440 --> 00:25:16,759
Excuse me. We urgently need a boat.

240
00:25:16,760 --> 00:25:18,479
May we rent yours?

241
00:25:18,480 --> 00:25:21,439
Whatever you want for your time,
we're willing to pay.

242
00:25:21,440 --> 00:25:22,639
This boat belongs to my boss.

243
00:25:22,640 --> 00:25:26,440
He asked me
to bring it here for his friend.

244
00:25:29,600 --> 00:25:30,840
He's here now.

245
00:25:32,280 --> 00:25:33,120
- Mr. Phum.
- Hello, Mr. Phum.

246
00:25:35,320 --> 00:25:37,560
You still haven't gone to Skull Island?

247
00:25:38,440 --> 00:25:39,639
We couldn't find a boat.

248
00:25:39,640 --> 00:25:41,040
No one would take us there.

249
00:25:43,800 --> 00:25:46,320
If you don't mind,
you're welcome to come with me.

250
00:25:47,800 --> 00:25:49,319
Sir, my boss asked me to tell you

251
00:25:49,320 --> 00:25:51,679
he'll coordinate with the police

252
00:25:51,680 --> 00:25:53,600
and have them follow you
to Skull Island as soon as possible.

253
00:25:56,040 --> 00:25:59,400
But if you despise me that much,
you can wait and go with the officers.

254
00:26:03,080 --> 00:26:04,280
I'm going with you.

255
00:26:05,120 --> 00:26:06,080
Please.

256
00:26:17,800 --> 00:26:18,959
- Dear.
- Dad.

257
00:26:18,960 --> 00:26:21,040
Dear, what's wrong?

258
00:26:22,440 --> 00:26:23,440
I'm fine.

259
00:26:25,560 --> 00:26:26,399
- Dad.
- Dear.

260
00:26:26,400 --> 00:26:27,439
- Dear.
- Dad.

261
00:26:27,440 --> 00:26:28,359
Call an ambulance now.

262
00:26:28,360 --> 00:26:29,279
- Yes.
- Dad.

263
00:26:29,280 --> 00:26:30,840
Dear.

264
00:26:38,120 --> 00:26:39,120
AMBULANCE SERVICE

265
00:26:39,800 --> 00:26:40,800
Prepare to lift.

266
00:26:49,480 --> 00:26:51,360
I'll take care of Dad.

267
00:26:51,920 --> 00:26:54,039
Na, you have to bring your sister back.

268
00:26:54,040 --> 00:26:55,120
Yes, Mom.

269
00:26:55,760 --> 00:26:57,319
Thank you very much, Mr. Phum.

270
00:26:57,320 --> 00:26:58,320
My pleasure.

271
00:26:58,840 --> 00:27:00,080
I'm going now.

272
00:27:12,640 --> 00:27:14,039
Don't worry.

273
00:27:14,040 --> 00:27:16,039
My friend owns this hospital.

274
00:27:16,040 --> 00:27:16,960
I've already coordinated with him.

275
00:27:17,680 --> 00:27:19,560
Your father will receive
the best care possible.

276
00:27:21,280 --> 00:27:22,400
Thank you very much.

277
00:27:22,920 --> 00:27:25,000
Let's go do our part.

278
00:27:25,600 --> 00:27:26,600
Wait, Mr. Phum.

279
00:27:27,240 --> 00:27:28,679
I know a shortcut

280
00:27:28,680 --> 00:27:30,679
to Skull Island.

281
00:27:30,680 --> 00:27:32,360
Would you let me drive the boat?

282
00:27:34,400 --> 00:27:36,560
With a sea captain
standing right in front of me,

283
00:27:37,200 --> 00:27:39,519
I'd be a fool to say no. Let's go.

284
00:27:39,520 --> 00:27:41,000
- Yes.
- Go prepare the boat.

285
00:29:13,040 --> 00:29:15,319
Hey. Men.

286
00:29:15,320 --> 00:29:16,480
You...

287
00:29:34,480 --> 00:29:37,160
<i>You dare abuse your dark magic</i>

288
00:29:37,680 --> 00:29:40,680
<i>and desecrate
the treasures of the kingdom.</i>

289
00:29:41,240 --> 00:29:44,800
<i>You shall be punished accordingly.</i>

290
00:29:46,080 --> 00:29:47,160
Who are you?!

291
00:29:48,120 --> 00:29:51,240
Who dares challenge me?!

292
00:30:36,040 --> 00:30:37,080
Son.

293
00:31:31,640 --> 00:31:33,560
I'll never give up!

294
00:31:36,640 --> 00:31:39,400
I will become what I once was again

295
00:31:40,160 --> 00:31:42,920
no matter how many people I have to kill!

296
00:31:49,000 --> 00:31:50,160
Kaimook,

297
00:31:51,440 --> 00:31:54,120
you're going to stay with me forever.

298
00:32:18,080 --> 00:32:19,440
Where could it have gone?

299
00:32:20,480 --> 00:32:22,160
When I arrived on the island,

300
00:32:22,720 --> 00:32:24,320
it was still here.

301
00:32:27,480 --> 00:32:28,720
Under the bed?

302
00:32:30,520 --> 00:32:33,360
Did I drop it?

303
00:32:35,560 --> 00:32:36,800
It's not here.

304
00:33:58,600 --> 00:33:59,600
Dad.

305
00:34:02,120 --> 00:34:03,040
Sarai.

306
00:34:04,520 --> 00:34:05,840
Sarai, my girl.

307
00:34:30,800 --> 00:34:32,760
I saw that female ghost again.

308
00:34:36,040 --> 00:34:37,280
Where is she now?

309
00:34:43,400 --> 00:34:44,480
She's waiting over there.

310
00:34:47,280 --> 00:34:48,600
Hurry and follow her.

311
00:35:15,240 --> 00:35:17,040
Since when has there been a ship here?

312
00:35:17,840 --> 00:35:18,840
Exactly.

313
00:35:20,520 --> 00:35:23,240
I'm sure it wasn't here during the day.

314
00:35:26,360 --> 00:35:28,840
Or is this the pirate ship?

315
00:35:33,200 --> 00:35:35,200
That female ghost is on the ship.

316
00:35:43,920 --> 00:35:46,920
Or maybe Kaimook
is being held on that ship?

317
00:35:52,080 --> 00:35:54,160
Hey, there's a rowboat over there.

318
00:37:08,600 --> 00:37:10,720
We should split up and search.

319
00:37:11,400 --> 00:37:12,760
You go with Ms. Da.

320
00:37:13,280 --> 00:37:15,280
I agree.

321
00:37:19,440 --> 00:37:21,840
Ms. Da, Ms. Da.

322
00:37:24,760 --> 00:37:27,120
She must be stressed, so she fainted.

323
00:37:30,000 --> 00:37:30,880
Then,

324
00:37:31,640 --> 00:37:33,039
you stay here and look after her.

325
00:37:33,040 --> 00:37:34,680
I'll search for Kaimook myself.

326
00:37:35,360 --> 00:37:36,480
Be careful.

327
00:37:41,400 --> 00:37:43,200
Ms. Da.

328
00:38:16,240 --> 00:38:17,280
No.

329
00:38:17,960 --> 00:38:20,080
I can't give up hope.

330
00:38:21,520 --> 00:38:23,080
There has to be a way.

331
00:38:24,240 --> 00:38:25,680
I have to get out.

332
00:38:55,840 --> 00:38:56,760
Kaimook.

333
00:39:18,520 --> 00:39:19,560
Ms. Da,

334
00:39:20,200 --> 00:39:21,200
how are you feeling?

335
00:39:23,760 --> 00:39:25,400
What happened to me?

336
00:39:25,960 --> 00:39:27,679
You were probably under too much stress

337
00:39:27,680 --> 00:39:30,440
from following that female ghost,
so you fainted.

338
00:39:32,720 --> 00:39:33,880
Female ghost?

339
00:39:34,440 --> 00:39:36,760
When did I follow her?
Why don't I remember anything?

340
00:39:43,880 --> 00:39:45,399
Where are we?

341
00:39:45,400 --> 00:39:47,400
This isn't my room at the research center.

342
00:39:49,440 --> 00:39:51,960
Ms. Da, we're on a ship.

343
00:39:52,560 --> 00:39:56,120
You were the one who led Thon and me here.

344
00:40:15,960 --> 00:40:17,399
I saw a ghost in my room.

345
00:40:17,400 --> 00:40:18,959
The same ghost that took Kaimook.

346
00:40:18,960 --> 00:40:20,399
It lunged at me

347
00:40:20,400 --> 00:40:23,040
and after that, I don't remember anything.

348
00:40:24,680 --> 00:40:27,200
Are you saying
you were possessed by a ghost?

349
00:40:27,720 --> 00:40:29,080
Yes.

350
00:40:29,640 --> 00:40:31,280
We fell into its trap.

351
00:40:34,800 --> 00:40:35,880
Now we're screwed.

352
00:41:13,320 --> 00:41:14,360
Kaimook,

353
00:41:15,400 --> 00:41:16,480
where are you?

354
00:41:27,160 --> 00:41:28,240
What's happening?

355
00:42:00,520 --> 00:42:02,120
We're screwed.

356
00:42:02,640 --> 00:42:04,080
That ghost tricked us onto this ship.

357
00:42:04,600 --> 00:42:06,000
What do you mean?

358
00:42:06,880 --> 00:42:08,439
It possessed Ms. Da.

359
00:42:08,440 --> 00:42:10,040
She didn't even know she came here.

360
00:42:11,480 --> 00:42:13,359
It's trying to kill us for sure.

361
00:42:13,360 --> 00:42:14,880
What are we going to do?

362
00:42:18,480 --> 00:42:20,840
We have to stop the ship first.

363
00:42:22,200 --> 00:42:24,040
Come. Follow me.

364
00:42:38,400 --> 00:42:40,079
Is that Skull Island ahead?

365
00:42:40,080 --> 00:42:41,000
Yes.

366
00:42:42,240 --> 00:42:44,000
I think we shouldn't approach
from the front side.

367
00:42:45,040 --> 00:42:46,159
Why not?

368
00:42:46,160 --> 00:42:48,799
We don't know what's happening
on the island right now.

369
00:42:48,800 --> 00:42:51,440
If we go in from the front,
we might become targets.

370
00:42:54,400 --> 00:42:57,319
You're very cautious.

371
00:42:57,320 --> 00:43:00,080
Then I'll steer around
to the side of the island instead.

372
00:43:10,080 --> 00:43:11,240
Do you know how to drive a ship?

373
00:43:11,880 --> 00:43:13,720
- No.
- What do we do now?

374
00:43:22,360 --> 00:43:24,959
This is bad!

375
00:43:24,960 --> 00:43:25,920
An island!

376
00:43:26,440 --> 00:43:27,920
The ship's gonna crash into the island!

377
00:43:30,080 --> 00:43:31,480
There's no time.

378
00:43:32,120 --> 00:43:34,200
We have to stop the ship
before it crashes into the island.

379
00:43:38,440 --> 00:43:41,240
It's so stiff. It won't budge at all.

380
00:43:43,520 --> 00:43:46,200
Hurry up! What are you guys doing?!

381
00:43:47,200 --> 00:43:49,040
I'm using all my strength.

382
00:44:07,760 --> 00:44:10,360
You'll all die!

383
00:44:11,600 --> 00:44:14,360
There's no way you can help Kaimook.

384
00:44:41,840 --> 00:44:44,160
Mr. Narathon, Mr. Phum.

385
00:44:44,680 --> 00:44:45,600
Don't go there, Kaimook.

386
00:45:43,680 --> 00:45:44,760
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
